# Zod validation (webapp)

See also: **`api-layer.mdc`** (where schemas live vs types/services/queries), **`frontend-security.mdc`** (client validation is not authorization).

## Core rule

**`parse()` / `safeParse()` at every entry point** (forms, URL/query builders, response validation when shape is critical). Use **`z.infer<typeof schema>`** for types. **No type assertions** (`as Foo`), no “trust me” casts. The schema **is** the contract.

| Boundary                    | Where to parse                                       |
| --------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| Form submit / modal confirm | `@/api/features/<domain>/*.schema` before `mutate`   |
| Client-side preflight       | Same schema as API body when possible                |
| `import.meta.env`           | Parse once in `src/api/config.ts` when you add more keys (see `zod-validation.mdc`) |
| Untrusted API payloads      | Optional `parse()` when runtime safety matters       |

## Shared primitives (`src/api/schema/primitives.schema.ts`)

Import these instead of redefining ad hoc:

| Primitive                    | Use for                                  |
| ---------------------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| `nonEmptyString`             | Titles, rules, display names             |
| `isoDate`                    | Timestamps from API                      |
| `positiveId`                 | Numeric form/query ids                   |
| `safeUrl`                    | Reference links, asset URLs — HTTPS-only |
| `enumFromObject(LABELS)`     | Enums synced to a const object           |
| `paginatedQuerySchema`       | List fetch params                        |
| `paginationMetaSchema`       | Validate `meta` on paginated responses   |
| `paginatedItemsSchema(item)` | Validate `{ items: T[] }` in `data`      |

```typescript
import { nonEmptyString, safeUrl, paginatedQuerySchema } from '@/api/schema/primitives.schema'

export const myFormSchema = z.object({
  title: nonEmptyString,
  referenceLinks: z.array(safeUrl).optional(),
})

export type MyFormValues = z.infer<typeof myFormSchema>
```

## Env (`src/api/config.ts`)

- This template reads `VITE_API_URL` directly. When you add more env keys, parse `import.meta.env` with Zod at module load — same pattern as a backend `src/lib/env.ts`.
- Only `VITE_*` keys; never put secrets in the browser bundle.

## nullable vs optional (pick deliberately)

| Zod           | Meaning                                           | Example |
| ------------- | ------------------------------------------------- | ------- |
| `.optional()` | Field **not in form state** / omitted from PATCH  |
| `.nullable()` | Field explicitly **cleared** (`null` sent to API) |
| `.nullish()`  | Both absent and null acceptable                   |

When backend accepts `null` to clear JSON fields, frontend patch schemas must use `.nullable()`, not `.optional()` alone.

## Pagination

- Query builders: extend **`paginatedQuerySchema`**.
- Types: `PaginationMeta` in `@/api/types/global.types.ts` aligns with backend `meta`.
- Prefer typed hooks; use **`paginationMetaSchema.parse(meta)`** only when validating unknown runtime data.

## Anti-patterns

```typescript
// ❌ Schema defined in pages/
// pages/FooPage.tsx — z.object({ ... })

// ❌ Inline z.string().trim().min(1) on every field

// ❌ Manual enum duplicated from labels/constants
status: z.enum(['draft', 'published'])

// ❌ Cast instead of parse
const body = input as CreateResourceFormInput
```

```typescript
// ✅ Page imports schema
import { myFormSchema, type MyFormValues } from '@/api/features/foo/foo.schema'

const parsed = myFormSchema.safeParse(formState)
if (!parsed.success) {
  /* surface field errors */ return
}
mutate(parsed.data)
```

## File layout

- **`src/api/features/<domain>/<domain>.schema.ts`** — domain Zod; export schema + `z.infer` types.
- **`src/api/schema/primitives.schema.ts`** — shared building blocks only.
- **`src/api/types/global.types.ts`** — shared TypeScript wrappers; feature DTO types live in **`features/<domain>/`**.
- **`src/lib/<domain>/`** — mappers, message helpers, submit orchestration — **not** Zod definitions.
